Full Description: PEG is in the business of manufacturing, and selling its proprietary IBR (Induced Bed Reactor) AD system for a variety of food and beverage firms that generate at least 12,000 tons of high-solid liquid organic wastes per year. The PEG IBR is a cost effective digester that takes high solid organic wastes and converts it into renewable energy to be consumed by the generator site as well as produce a marketable fertilizer from the resultant digested nutrient rich fiber filled liquid.    The core of PEGâs business will be the industrial and commercial market sectors, which can benefit by on-site energy production and reduced off-site organic waste disposal. PEG will market its IBR systems, which it will design and build as complete AD package units so that the entire AD plant and its peripheral equipment are a stand-alone unitary system. By designing and building its AD systems as complete units, PEG will be able to offer the commercial and industrial market sectors standardized systems that integrate well with various process equipment found in plants and factories.     To serve Pure Energy Group (PEG) is dedicated to developing waste to energy systems for the industrial and commercial market place through the use of patented and proprietary anaerobic digestion technology (AD). By means of licensing patented Induced Bed Reactor (IBR) anaerobic digestion (AD) technology from Utah State University, PEG has secured exclusive worldwide rights to develop, market, sell and install IBR systems for industrial and commercial clients. The IBR technology and design is unique among competing AD systems by virtue of being much smaller in size and physical footprint while being able to process/digest waste streams of higher solids to liquid ratios. These embodiments as well as various enhancements make the IBR technology much more adaptable to current and growing industry demands where space constraints and process efficiency are of great concern to system operators.

Description: BioPhotonic Solutions is a developer and manufacturer of pulse shapers for ultrafast lasers.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: BioPhotonic Solutions, Inc. develops and manufactures pulse shapers for ultrafast lasers. Its products include pixel phase or phase-amplitude ultrashort pulse shapers; commercial three-in-one ultrashort pulse shapers; and a pulse shaping system to perform spectral-phase characterization, and compensate spectral-phase distortions to obtain transform-limited pulses and deliver phase-shaped pulses. The company also provides ultrafast optics products, microscope detection units, ultrathin SHG crystal MCUO-SHG products, and ultra broadband mirror and MCUO-mirror products; and femtoPulse Master&trade, a simulation software solution to calculate in temporal and spectral domain. It offers commercial 4f pulse shapers based on multiphoton intrapulse interference phase scan technology that provide phase characterization, pulse measurement, compression, and arbitrary pulse shaping solutions within a device. The company offers its products for biomedical imaging, two-photon microscopy, and dispersion measurements on dielectric mirrors applications, as well as for material processing, micro machining, two-photon microscopy, surgical applications, proteomic and metabolomic analysis, coherent laser control, time-resolved measurements, filamentation studies, attosecond sciences, THZ spectroscopy, and high harmonic generation applications. It offers its products through distribution contracts with laser companies in the United States and internationally. BioPhotonic Solutions, Inc. was founded in 2003 and is based in East Lansing, Michigan.

Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Condaptive is a mobile startup focused on the maximizing the value of location. To derive the full benefit of location, you have to also understand what that user is looking for and make it really easy for them to find. This is our focus with Condaptive. Our mission is to make it easy for developers and marketers to build location-centric experiences that focus not just on where their customers are, but also on who they are and what they need. We provide a complete technology platform that makes it effortless for anyone to build location and context aware applications.
